x4freetext: Last checking has been done.
Neon gas enriched to 99% in Ne-22 was recirculated in
a differentially pumped gas target system of the
extended type.  The gas composition was monitored with
mass spectrometer, as well as via the He-4 elastic
scattering from the target gas.
85-cm**3 intrinic Ge-detector for E(a) <=
80-cm**3 Ge(Li) and 123-cm**3 Ge(Li) detector.
Energy resolution of these detectors were in the range
2.1 to 3.5-KeV at E(G) =1.33-MeV.
Gridded ionization chamber of cylindrical shape
the energy resolution of the spectrometers was about
30-KeV for thermal neutrons and about 90-KeV for MeV-
neutrons.
Since normal charge integration measurements at
the Faraday cup are made difficult by charge- exchange
effects of the incident ions in the gas target the
number of incident projectiles was determined from the
alpha+Ne-22 elastic scattering yield, observed at angle
30 degree.
-By compiler. Data-heading in the data-section EN is
the effective beam energy at the center of the target
chamber.
The 4-MV dynamitron accelerator.
A 4-He+ beam with particle current up to 250
microamperes at the target.
